Vegan Peanut Rice Noodles
  --America's Test Kitchen

Sauce:
1 tbsp vegetable oil
2 thai, serrano, or jalapeno chiles, stemmed, seeded, and minced
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 tbsp grated fresh ginger
1 1/2 tsp curry powder
1/2 c water + extra as needed
1/3 c creamy peanut butter
3 tbsp seasoned rice vinegar
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp sugar

Heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat until shimmering. Stir in chilies, garlic, ginger, and curry powder and cook until fragrant, ~ 30 s. Stir in water, peanut butter, vinegar, shoyu, and sugar, and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened and flavors meld, ~ 2 min. Adjust consistency as needed with additional water. Transfer to a bowl.

Noodles:
1 c shredded carrots
2 tbsp seasoned rice vinegar
12 oz (1/4" wide) rice noodles
3 tbsp vegetable oil
1 c frozen edamame
sauce
1 c shredded red cabbage
1/3 c dry roasted peanuts, chopped (garnish)
2 tbsp torn fresh basil (garnish)
lime wedges (garnish)

Combine carrots and vinegar in a small bowl; set aside. Cover noodles with very hot tap water in large bowl and stir to separate. Let noodles soak until softened, pliable, and limp but not fully tender, ~20 min. Drain noodles. Heat 1 tbsp oil in 12" skillet over medium high heat until just smoking. Add edamame and cook until spotty brown but still bright green, ~2 min; transfer to bowl. In now empty skillet, heat remaining 2 tbsp oil over medium heat until shimmering, add noodles, 1 1/4 c water, 1/2 c sauce and cook until sauce has thickened slightly and noodles are well coated and tender, ~1 min. Divide noodles among indivdual serving bowls, top with carrots, edamame, and cabbage. Drizzle with remaining sauce, sprinkle with peanuts and basil, and serve with lime wedges.
